Key Match Events: Bobby Witt Jr. beat out an infield single to drive in the go-ahead run
Post-Match Reflections: Michael Massey said the front office bringing in experienced veterans with previous playoff experience like Tommy Pham, Yuli Gurriel, Michael Wacha, and Will Smith made this possible
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Royals left 12 runners on base and got through another close game with a razor-thin margin for error thanks to some masterful managing by Matt Quatraro
Others: The Orioles were swept in their only playoff series for a second consecutive year, going 1 for 13 with runners in scoring position this time and 5 for 32 combined
